node.text: The speed of innovation is accelerating at a pace faster than ever before. At Intuit, we believe in using emerging technologies to power prosperity around the world, and we use these innovations to solve complex problems at the heart of economic opportunities for small business owners, self-employed professionals, and millions of customers looking to improve their financial freedom and literacy.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Being an intern is your superpower. Once you tell someone you're an intern, they will go out of their way to help you and support you. Emma Anderson Software Engineer Intern Class '18&'19 19 She/Her'.

node.text: As companies continue to embrace virtual internships, Intuit pulls out all the stops to ensure the best experience. Hear from four of our interns about what that looked like for them. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 26, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'As we consider where we want to go, it's never been more important for all of us to dream big, work hard and embrace the unknown. Sasan Goodarzi CEO He/Him/His'.

node.text: Internships are a stepping stone for the next chapter of any career. Head to the link in our bio for the three lessons our CEO Sasan Goodarzi shared with our own interns.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Scott's t-shirt business grew 14% in 2020, despite the pandemic and a limited social media presence. He credits the success to his relationships in the community, such as the one he has with our local Prosperity Hub program partner.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text: Corey felt empowered to grow in all aspects of his life, including at his job as an Intuit technical agent through our Prosperity Hub program. Supported by leaders that believed in him, he went on to be the site’s team manager and then was promoted to team lead.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, outdoors and tree.

node.text: Melissa understands the power of a company believing in and uplifting her community. Our goal is to bring rewarding job opportunities to places that need them so that we can make a difference in more lives.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'I'm in love with entrepreneurship. I'm ın love with solving problems. And most of all, I'm really in love with what can become. Jason Hendricks Founder of Forgot or Knot'.

node.text: We're powering student success for life outside the classroom through @QuickBooks. It's stories like Jason's that remind us why these programs are vital for new entrepreneurs.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Intuit on July 12, 2021 tagging @quickbooks. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Powering student success for life through QuickBooks'.

node.text: Intuit is committed to turning big ambitions into prosperous realities. We’re partnering with educators to provide real-world tools like @quickbooks for free. Students can get the knowledge, skills, and certifications to stand out while preparing for the new world of work.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on July 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'z z 安 z Hitting Snooze to support our employees'.

node.text:
Mental health matters. As part of our company-wide days to support our employees’ well-being, we’ll be taking a snooze on social media this week so that our team around the world has the opportunity to disconnect from work.

We’re still here for our customers — Intuit support teams will be rotating their time off to ensure we’re available to help with any care needs.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on June 30, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'LGBTQ+ TERMS 101 Nonbinary When a person's gender identity doesn't fit inside traditional male or female categories Pride Month'.

node.text: Being nonbinary means different things to different people. For instance, not all nonbinary people use they/them pronouns — some use she, he, and/or they, while some use something different altogether. Staying respectful and supportive are vital to fostering an inclusive culture. #Pride

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on June 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'It's gigantic hug ofempathy. It's the commitment to a person S well-being and a right to live as fully as have been afforded. Being an ally is an act of love and kindness in the hope of a better tomorrow for all. Jim Graziano Pronouns He/Him/His'.

node.text: We work each day to foster a culture of inclusion here at Intuit. We know that this requires active and conscious effort from everyone, and that starts with allyship. Learn what allyship with the LGBTQ+ community can look like from a few of our employees through the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Intuit on June 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'LGBTQ+ TERMS 101 Transgender A general term used to describe someone whose gender identity is different than the sex assigned at birth. Pride Month'.

node.text: A person's gender expression doesn't say anything about their gender identity. It's important to normalize different gender identities in the workplace, especially through small gestures like encouraging all employees to share their pronouns. #Pride

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Intuit on June 28, 2021 tagging @canadian_women_in_food, and @quickbooks. May be an image of dessert and text that says 'PREMIUM HANDMADE Classic cocoa butter CHOCOLATE HotShot Hot Shot CHOCOLATE hand milk painted colours with chocolate bar 34% MILK RAINBOW Pride Month CHOCOLATE FLAG'.

node.text: @Canadian_women_in_food is creating a more meaningful way to shop by promoting women-owned businesses and amplifying the voices of female food entrepreneurs. This @quickbooks customer is helping foster a more inclusive space for all women in food.
